div.h1: Trace Example: SELECT * FROM users WHERE id > 5

p.strong: Step-by-step execution through the entire query pipeline

div.p: Key Instruction: Le 0 8 - If id <= 5, jump to address 8 (Next) This skips ResultRow for non-matching rows
Address 4: Le r0 r1 Jump to 8 if r0 <= r1
Row 1 (id=3): 3 <= 5 TRUE JUMP (skip output) Row 2 (id=7): 7 <= 5 FALSE Continue to output Row 3 (id=2): 2 <= 5 TRUE JUMP (skip output)
The conditional jump is the WHERE clause in action! Each row's id is tested; only rows passing the test reach the ResultRow instruction.

g.text: Position before first; jump to 10 if empty
PC=1: Rewind cursor positioned before row 1
